{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Zec|2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","chapter":2,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:2:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":2,"verse":1,"text":"I looked up and saw a man with a measuring line in his hand.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:2:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":2,"verse":2,"text":"I asked, “Where are you going?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:2:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":2,"verse":3,"text":"Then the angel who was speaking with me went out, and another angel went out to meet him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:2:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":2,"verse":4,"text":"He said to him, “Run and tell this young man: Jerusalem will be inhabited without walls because of the number of people and animals in it.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:2:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":2,"verse":5,"text":"The declaration of the Lord: “I myself will be a wall of fire around it, and I will be the glory within it.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:2:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":2,"verse":6,"text":"“Listen! Listen! Flee from the land of the north” —this is the Lord’s declaration —“for I have scattered you like the four winds of heaven” —this is the Lord’s declaration.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:2:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":2,"verse":7,"text":"“Listen, Zion! Escape, you who are living with Daughter Babylon.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:2:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":2,"verse":8,"text":"For the Lord of Armies says this: “In pursuit of his glory, he sent me against the nations plundering you, for whoever touches you touches the pupil of my eye.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:2:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":2,"verse":9,"text":"For look, I am raising my hand against them, and they will become plunder for their own servants. Then you will know that the Lord of Armies has sent me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:2:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":2,"verse":10,"text":"“Daughter Zion, shout for joy and be glad, for I am coming to dwell among you” —this is the Lord’s declaration.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:2:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":2,"verse":11,"text":"“Many nations will join themselves to the Lord on that day and become my people. I will dwell among you, and you will know that the Lord of Armies has sent me to you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:2:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":2,"verse":12,"text":"The Lord will take possession of Judah as his portion in the Holy Land, and he will once again choose Jerusalem.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:2:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":2,"verse":13,"text":"Let all humanity be silent before the Lord, for from his holy dwelling he has roused himself.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","chapter":2,"paragraphStarts":[1,3,6,10],"head